#: content/docs/password-managers.md:0
msgid "Use Password Managers with Web Browsers"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:14
msgid ""
"KDE Linux ships web browsers as Flatpak packages, which prevents 3rd-party "
"password managers such as 1Password and KeePassXC from communicating with "
"their browser extensions until they implement support for the [“Flatpak XDG "
"Native Messaging Proxy“ protocol](https://github.com/flatpak/xdg-native-"
"messaging-proxy). To date, neither has done so."
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:16
msgid ""
"No simple solution currently exists to remedy this issue on KDE Linux. "
"General users are recommended to choose a different method of managing "
"passwords."
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:18
msgid ""
"**Options presented here are suitable only for advanced users comfortable "
"with tinkering and recovering from breakage.**"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:21
msgid "1Password"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:22
msgid ""
"1Password may be made able to communicate with its browser extension by "
"installing it using Nix, Distrobox, or [manually using this "
"script](https://github.com/rudidev08/1password-browser-integration-on-kde-"
"linux/blob/main/1password-flatpak-browser-integration.sh)."
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:25
msgid "KeePassXC"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:26
msgid ""
"Various options for making KeePassXC able to communicate with its browser "
"extension can be found at the following websites:"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:27
msgid "https://www.snamellit.com/blog/keepassxc-and-flatpak"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:28
msgid ""
"https://discourse.flathub.org/t/how-to-run-firefox-and-keepassxc-in-a-"
"flatpak-and-get-the-keepassxc-browser-add-on-to-work/437"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:31
msgid "Help improve the situation"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:32
msgid ""
"Please consider providing feedback to password manager developers and "
"browser vendors asking them to improve support for immutable operating "
"systems and native messaging between Flatpak-sandboxed apps, and Flatpak "
"support in general."
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:34
msgid "See also:"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:35
msgid "https://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/flatpak/2025-April/002386.html"
msgstr ""

#: content/docs/password-managers.md:36
